# Trivyignore file for managing false positives in vulnerability scanning
# Format: CVE ID or vulnerability identifier followed by reason and expiration

# Example entries (uncomment and modify as needed):
# CVE-2023-12345
#   exp: 2025-12-31
#   reason: "This vulnerability is not applicable to our usage"

# To generate and manage these:
# 1. Run: trivy fs . --severity HIGH,CRITICAL
# 2. Review false positives
# 3. Add to this file with justification
# 4. Set expiration dates for review
